      <description>&lt;span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;hr&gt;Xianzu_Monk_Tunare wrote:&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;What you all fail to realize is that Tradeskill items will be bought and removed from the lists.  The non tradeskill items get to sit there until the vendors are full of them and never change till the server reset or a zone crash.&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;Why don't you buy all the cheap stuff from vendors you want to vendor mine and then sell it back to some vendor you don't care about it (or even just destroy it). Not as good as having a complete vendor reset and wastes a little cash, but better than nothing.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Another, similar, method that works for common items is to seed vendors. For example, when I was skilling up Poison Making I needed a ton of Phosporous Powder and Golden Ember Powder. Phosporous was as common as dirt but Golden Ember was considerably more difficult. In order to increase the chance of mining Golden Ember I sold a single piece of the powder to all the major vendors in PoK. I checked back once/twice a day and bought all the extra powder (save one). Works great but certainly not possible with more expensive components.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
