      <title>Re: Merchant fix maybe...</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&amp;message.id=9784#M9784</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;/cheer&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The vendor mine trick minus one is an easy solution to keep merchant seeded. I use it extensively. Alas other miners aren't as thoughtfull about it and sometimes buy out the stock. In some cases it is worth reseeding, in others not. It is a form of playercontrol over merchant stock- same as killing a merchant to reset.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;And yes the nitpicking got to a high level.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Items i vendor mined (non tradeskill flagged)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- Mask of obteneration;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- Iksar illusion mask&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- Various quest pieces like dansk blossom/Dansk branch/Kyv bowstring which sell for decent amounts of pp&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- High tribute items with relatively low merchant value (look at the lists that float around)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- various spells in the lvl 50-60 range for my cleric and wizard&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;About unflagged items: When notified they get fixed (eventually) so what wasn't flagged 3 months or 6 months ago can very well be flagged now.  Most people that encounter a recipe which needs an unflagged item will keep this relatively quiet to facilitate vendor mining. Eventually these filter out though and then get corrected&lt;/p&gt;</description>
